President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate Brian Hayes as a member of the National Labor Relations Board (NLRB). Hayes currently serves as the Republican Labor Policy Director for the U.S. Senate Committee on Health, Education, Labor and Pensions. He has over 25 years of experience in private legal practice, exclusively representing management clients in labor and employment law cases. Hayes has argued labor cases before federal courts, negotiated labor contracts, and counseled clients on compliance with labor laws. He earned his undergraduate degree from Boston College and his law degree from Georgetown University Law Center.